【翻訳】
Things that can be determined about the arsenal through astrology, including things about the Contest  (battle?) at Nagasaka Nodoka Mumenmoku\
\
One: From the 12th year of Eiroku (The year of the snake, _tsuchinoto-no-mi_) to the seventh month of following year of the Ox, in the heavens, a star that lets off smoke (a comet?) appeared.  A widely-studied man from Kōshū's (Shiga Pref.) Ishi-dera was sent for by \[Takeda\] Shingen from the time he was the age of 31. In the past,  by the flow of clearness (a shooting star?), he had been a fortune-teller. 
Within that \[fortune telling\] there was a prophesy(?), and by his ability to tell fortunes, he was(?) called "the arsenal of prophesies."
His fortune-telling was supported by the True Dharma, and contained both the "inner texts \[of Buddhism\]" and the "outer \[non-Buddhist\] texts," and if there were not even a little  evil spirits/curses, in the county of Minochi in Shinshū (Nagano Pref.), distributed land \[of a value of\] a hundred "strings of cash" was given \[to him\] in perpetuity, 

